```

## Where SAM differs from agentmemory

| Dimension | agentmemory | SAM |
|---|---|---|
| Domain | Coding agents | Sales agents |
| Capture hooks | `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart` | `OnEmailSent`, `OnReplyReceived`, `OnMeetingScheduled`, `OnSignalDetected` (v0.2+) |
| Entities | Sessions, Observations, Memories | Account, Stakeholder, OutreachThread, Touch, Meeting, Signal, Hypothesis, Qualification, WarmRoute |
| Tier 4 vocabulary | working/episodic/semantic/procedural | L0 raw / L1 atoms / L2 scenes / L3 persona |
| Retrieval | BM25 + vector + knowledge graph (RRF) | SQLite + markdown grep (v0.1); vector + RRF (v0.2+) |
| Stack | TypeScript / iii-engine / SQLite | Python / pydantic / SQLite |

The shape is the same. The vocabulary, schemas, and capture moments are sales-native rather than dev-native.

## Roadmap

**v0.1.0 (this release)** — Schemas, SQLite storage, 4-tier markdown layer, CLI, examples, docs.

**v0.2.0** — Vector embeddings (sentence-transformers, local) + BM25 + RRF fusion. Replaces the v0.1 markdown grep with hybrid semantic search.

**v0.3.0** — MCP server. 7+ core tools (`sam_account_get`, `sam_stakeholder_search`, `sam_touch_log`, `sam_scene_read`, `sam_persona_get`, `sam_qualify_update`, `sam_signal_record`). Drop-in for Claude Code, Cursor, etc.

**v0.4.0** — Capture hooks. `OnEmailSent` (Outlook/Gmail integration), `OnReplyReceived`, `OnMeetingScheduled` (calendar integration), `OnSignalDetected` (news/press scraping). Auto-populate L1 atoms from real-world events.

**v0.5.0** — LLM compression. Optional summarisation pass: raw L0 transcript → L1 atomic facts → L2 scene narrative. Pluggable provider (Anthropic / OpenAI / local).

**v1.0.0** — Knowledge graph. Stakeholder → Account → Partner → Competitor traversal. Surfaces second-order relationships ("who at Acme is connected to anyone in our portfolio?").

## Credits

SAM is **inspired by** [agentmemory](https://github.com/rohitg00/agentmemory) by Rohit Gangupantulu. The 4-tier consolidation model and the file-indexed storage philosophy are direct ports. The schemas, vocabulary, hooks, and CLI shape are SAM's own.

